19 ADD CERTAIN COMPOSTING FACILITIES TO THE DEFINITION OF
20 "AGRICULTURE"
21 SECTION 18. G.S. 106-581.1 reads as rewritten:
22 "§ 106-581.1. Agriculture defined.
23 For purposes of this Article, the terms "agriculture", "agricultural", and "farming" refer to all
24 of the following:
25 …
26 (8) The production, processing, storage, use, and sale of compost for agricultural,
27 residential, or commercial purposes by a permitted Small or Large Type 1,
28 Type 2, or Type 3 composting facility as defined in rules adopted by the
29 Environmental Management Commission. For the purposes of this section,
30 compost means a product made from organic plant, animal, or food waste and
31 created through controlled aerobic, biological decomposition of
32 biodegradable materials that, when subject to mesophilic and thermophilic
33 temperatures, stabilizes the carbon content, reduces the viability of pathogens
34 and vector attraction, and when added to soils is beneficial to plant growth."
