2 AUTHORIZE USE OF CERTAIN SUBSURFACE DISPERSAL PRODUCTS FOR
3 WASTEWATER STORAGE AND DISPERSAL IN TRAFFIC-RATED AREAS UNDER
4 PRIVATE OPTION PERMITS
5 SECTION 20.5. G.S. 130A-343 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
6 "(j3) Authorize Certain Subsurface Dispersal Products for Use in Traffic-Rated Areas
7 Under Private Option Permits. – A wastewater dispersal product approved pursuant to this
8 section shall be approved for use in wastewater storage and dispersal under areas subject to
9 vehicular traffic and traffic-bearing loads if a professional engineer, licensed pursuant to Chapter
10 89C of the General Statutes, certifies that the product has been designed with a compatible load
11 rating and the product manufacturer has approved the product for use in traffic-rated areas.
12 Wastewater permits issued pursuant to this subsection shall be issued by a professional engineer,
13 licensed pursuant to Chapter 89C of the General Statutes, under G.S. 130A-336.1, or by an
14 Authorized On-Site Wastewater Evaluator under G.S. 130A-336.2. For the purposes of this
15 section, "traffic-rated areas" does not include Department of Transportation rated areas but does
16 include driveways and private parking areas with impervious or pervious pavement areas."
17
18 PART II. SEVERABILITY CLAUSE AND EFFECTIVE DATE
19 SECTION 21. If any provision of this act or the application thereof to any person or
20 circumstances is held invalid, such invalidity shall not affect other provisions or applications of
21 this act that can be given effect without the invalid provision or application and, to this end, the
22 provisions of this act are declared to be severable.
23 SECTION 22. Except as otherwise provided, this act is effective when it becomes
24 law.
